And decided to take a closer look at New York:

# Libraries
library(ggplot2)
library(tidyverse)
library(sf)
library(maps)

new.york.map <- map_data("county", region = "new york")

# Explore xrel in New York -----------------------------------------------------

new.york.measles.rel <- new.york %>%
  filter(lng < 0) %>%
  drop_na(xrel) %>%
  ggplot() +
  geom_polygon(data = new.york.map, aes(long, lat, group = group), color = "lightgray", size = 0.1) + 
  geom_point(data = new.york, aes(lng, lat, colour = xrel), size = 0.5) + 
  scale_colour_viridis_c(option = "plasma", name = "Students exempted from vaccination \n for religious reasons (%)") + 
  facet_wrap(~type) + 
  theme_bw() + 
  theme(legend.position = "top")

new.york.measles.med <- new.york %>%
  filter(lng < 0) %>%
  drop_na(xmed) %>%
  ggplot() +
  geom_polygon(data = new.york.map, aes(long, lat, group = group), color = "lightgray", size = 0.1) + 
  geom_point(data = new.york, aes(lng, lat, colour = xmed), size = 0.5) + 
  scale_colour_viridis_c(option = "plasma", name = "Students exempted from vaccination \n for medical reasons (%)") + 
  facet_wrap(~type) + 
  theme_bw() + 
  theme(legend.position = "top")
